<br>
PvP With a penalty to the loser absolutly kills the &quot;casual gamer&quot; market.  If you play for 1 hr every 3 days, you DO NOT want to get PKed and lose your exp/cash/item/time/ear/whatever.  <br>
<br>
The Casual gamer market is where MMOLRPGs make thier money.  Not to say that games don't need hardcore gamers; without them, the masses don't have any Stars to strive to be.<br>
<br>
Considering the Content cutbacks that SWG is going through to make thier shipdate, I was hopeing it would inject some reality into the SWG Fanboys candyland.  Silly me, I forgot these are humans I'm talking about.<br>
<br>
Horizons has been vapor for Sooooo long.  But they seem to be meeting milestones now, and are crazy ambitious on thier ideals.  The only question is: will it be released before the graphics become outdated, and if it IS released in a timely manner, how much content/balancing/vision gets cut.<br>
<br>
Untill SOE gives EQ1 players the chance to import thier characters into EQ2 with gear/levels/cash/whatever, EQ2 will have to compete with EQ1 just like every other game out there (assuming SOE doesn't artifically distroy this competition by taking down EQ1 servers, making the game unplayable, or the like)<br>
